gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 146, Pistons 114
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks defeated the Pistons, 146-114. Damian Lillard led the way for the Bucks with 33 points, four rebounds, five assists and six 3PM, while Bobby Portis added a season-high 31 points and 12 rebounds in the victory. Bojan Bogdanovic (24 points) and Cade Cunningham (25 points, six assists) combined for 49 points for the Pistons in the losing effort. The Bucks win their third straight game as they improve to 18-7 on the season, while the Pistons fall to 2-24.
